2026-03-07 | Number of Ways to Get Sum with n Dice

	Question
Given n dice with m faces each, find the number of ways to obtain sum x.

	Approach
1.	Define DP state:
		dp[i][j] = number of ways to get sum j using i dice.
2.	Base case:
		dp[0][0] = 1  
		(0 dice forming sum 0)
3.	Transition:
		For each dice i
		For each possible sum j
		Try all face values f from 1..m
		If j ≥ f:
				dp[i][j] += dp[i-1][j-f]
4.	The final answer will be:
		dp[n][x]
5.	Time Complexity:
		O(n * x * m)
6.	Space Complexity:
		O(n * x)

	Solution

class Solution {
public:
    long long numberOfWays(int n, int m, int x) {
        vector<vector<long long>> dp(n + 1, vector<long long>(x + 1, 0));

        dp[0][0] = 1;

        for (int i = 1; i <= n; i++) {
            for (int sum = 1; sum <= x; sum++) {
                for (int face = 1; face <= m; face++) {
                    if (sum >= face)
                        dp[i][sum] += dp[i - 1][sum - face];
                }
            }
        }

        return dp[n][x];
    }
};

	Key Insight
This is a classic dynamic programming problem.
Each dice adds values 1..m to the sum,
so we build solutions incrementally
based on previous dice results.
